<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-01-08"><hi rend="italic">January 8,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Does proposed agreement call for more on part of President than
                            refraining from excluding Spanish products under act 1890 in
                            consideration of favored-nation treatment by Spain?</p>
